    "Dreyer owns about half of the Hasbergen, Germany based company, which has annual revenue of about $1 billion.",
    "Amazonen was established in 1883 by his great-grandfather, Heinrich Dreyer, who sold his first plow in 1894 and first cultivator in 1904.",
    "The company has paid shareholder dividends totaling of about 500 million euros since 2005."
